Generic single-database configuration.

# How to use it
1. Create a new database and a new user for it.
2. Copy this file to alembic.ini and edit it.
3. Run "alembic upgrade head" to create the tables.
4. Run "alembic revision --autogenerate -m "message"" to generate a new revision.
5. Run "alembic upgrade head" to apply the new revision.
6. Modify the models in models.py.
7. Go to step 4.
